{"type":"message","id":"f274644f","parentId":"02a580ed","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:19:42.686Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_tl2k0w41q4n2_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 151819\n\n## Applied Mutations\nJust applied: research/GAP-DECAY-MAPPING.md (appended)\n\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine what concrete action to take.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals and recent developments:\r\n\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 COMPLETE (architecture analysis, gap-decay synthesis)\r\n2. CFI Compression Experiment completed - found key insights about constant-format tokens\r\n3. Key pending item: Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C)\r\n   - Formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n   - Test if this distinguishes \"constant format\" from \"research trajectory\"\r\n\r\nThe most impactful next action is to run the Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment. This directly follows from the CFI compression synthesis and addresses the \"constant format problem\" they discovered.\r\n\r\nTo run this experiment, I need to:\r\n1. Analyze the pulse data to compute the hybrid scores\r\n2. Compare against binary thresholds\r\n3. Document results\r\n\r\nLet me create an experiment script and run it to generate results, then document in a new synthesis file.\r\n\r\nFirst, I need to check what data I have available. The pulses are in `research/pulses/` directory. I should look at the recent pulse data to compute CFI and frequency metrics.\r\n\r\nActually, looking at the structure, I need to:\r\n1. Get all pulse files\r\n2. Extract token frequencies and CFI values\r\n3. Compute hybrid scores\r\n4. Test the hypothesis\r\n\r\nLet me write a PowerShell script to do this analysis and run the experiment.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI Compression Experiment identified a critical insight: constant-format tokens (freq≈160, CFI=1.00) are metaprogramming artifacts that look causal but carry zero information. The next step is to implement and test the hybrid CFI×Freq scoring formula against this problem.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate and run the Hybrid CFI×Freq Scoring Experiment to test whether `score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)` successfully distinguishes constant-format tokens from true research trajectory tokens. Generate a new synthesis document with results.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Hybrid CFI×Freq Scoring Experiment\r\n**Date:** 2026-03-24\r\n**Status:** RUNNING\r\n\r\n## Experiment Design\r\n\r\n### Hypothesis\r\nThe hybrid formula `score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)` will:\r\n- Deweight constant-format tokens (freq≈160, CFI=1.00) → score ≈ 1.0 × 1.0 = 1.0 (but capped by freq/120 = 1.33, so score = 1.0)\r\n- Properly weight research trajectory tokens (freq<120, CFI>0.5) → score = CFI × (freq/120)\r\n\r\n### Token Categories Expected\r\n| Category | freq | CFI | Expected Score | Notes |\r\n|----------|------|-----|----------------|-------|\r\n| Constant format | ~160 | 1.00 | 1.00 (max) | TRAP - should be deweighted |\r\n| Research trajectory | 50-136 | 0.5-0.96 | 0.21-0.65 | True signal |\r\n| Rare but causal | 3-10 | 0.7-0.9 | 0.02-0.08 | Low frequency, high CFI |\r\n| Noise | <3 | <0.3 | <0.01 | Should be filtered |\r\n\r\n### Analysis Plan\r\n1. Extract all unique tokens from 200 pulse files\r\n2. Compute per-token frequency across all pulses\r\n3. Compute CFI (Conditional Format Invariance) for each token\r\n4. Calculate hybrid score using formula\r\n5. Compare scoring distribution against binary thresholds (CFI≥0.7 AND freq<120)\r\n\r\n## Results (TBD)\r\n\r\n### Dataset\r\n- Pulses analyzed: TBD\r\n- Unique tokens: TBD\r\n- Mean frequency: TBD\r\n- Mean CFI: TBD\r\n\r\n### Score Distribution\r\n```\r\n[Will populate after running experiment]\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Key Findings (TBD)\r\n\r\n## Conclusion (TBD)\r\n```\r\nfile: research/HYBRID_CFI_FREQ_EXPERIMENT.md\r\n```\r\n\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: ## Pending\r\n- [x] Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C) — RUNNING\r\n  - Formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n  - Test: does this distinguish \"constant format\" (freq≈160, CFI=1) from \"research trajectory\" (freq<120, CFI>0.5)?\r\n  - Run: 200 pulses, 80/20 split, compare against binary thresholds\r\n```\r\nfile: state/goals.md\r\n```\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 15:18:37\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774379982683}}
